HEADWORD: Poplin
<hw>Pop"lin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>popeline</ets>, <ets>papeline</ets>.]</ety> <def>A fabric of many
varieties, usually made of silk and worsted, -- used especially for
women's dresses.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Irish poplin</b></col>, <cd>a fabric with silk warp and
worsted weft, made in Ireland.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Popliteal</ent>⟦br⟧
